HEADWORD: Thermochrosy
<hw>Ther*moch"ro*sy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Thermo-</ets> + Gr. <?/ coloring.]</ety> <fld>(Physics)</fld>
<def>The property possessed by heat of being composed, like light, of
rays of different degrees of refrangibility, which are unequal in rate
or degree of transmission through diathermic substances.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

